<sect>Introduction
<p>

A <tt/RTS/ (real-time strategy game) was missing under linux, and we felt like
we could do it.  KDE/Qt appeared to be the best environment under which such a
game could be done.

We would like to thanx Warwick Allison (<htmlurl url="warwick@troll.no" name="warwick@troll.no">)
for his wonderful <tt/QwSpriteField/ library, which is used by Boson.  
We hope you will enjoy this game as much as we did while doing it and 
we would appreciate any suggestions and comments.

Please contact : <tt/Thomas Capricelli/
<htmlurl url="mailto:capricel@enst.fr" name="capricel@enst.fr">.
<p>

<p>
<sect1>Changes
<p>

Boson 0.1 is the first release, it's meant to be a developper-only release and
isn't yet intended for playing.

This release features :
<itemize>
	<item> Network layer and synchronisation.
	<item> Map file structure.
	<item> Selection and mutliple selection (control+click)
	<item> Units/Mobiles displaying.
	<item> One can <tt/move/ units
	<item> Units can move only on 'allowed' ground and don't overlap.
</itemize>

