<sect>Installation
<p>
<sect1>How to obtain Boson 
<p>

<bf/Boson/ can be found on <htmlurl
url="http://aquila.rezel.enst.fr/boson/" name="the boson homepage" >.

Until the first public release (should be 0.5), this is the only place you can find it. Then, it
will probably also be available on the main kde ftp site, and perhaps on some other places.

<sect1>Requirements
<p>
In order to successfully compile boson, you need kdelibs-1.0 and kdesupport-1.0, or the latest versions
of <tt> libkdecore</tt>, <tt> libkdeui</tt>, <tt> libkfile</tt>, <tt> libkfm</tt> and <tt> libQwSpriteField</tt>.
All required libraries can be found on <url url="ftp://ftp.kde.org/pub/kde/">.

<sect1>Compilation and installation
<p>

In order to compile and install Boson on your system, type the following in
the base directory of the Boson distribution:

<tscreen><verb>
% ./configure
% make
% make install
</verb></tscreen>

You will probably need to be root for the install stage.

<p>
Since Boson uses <tt/autoconf/ you should have not trouble
compiling it.
Should you run into problems please report them to the the author at 
<htmlurl url="mailto:capricel@enst.fr" name = "Thomas Capricelli">


